==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Solomons seal
<hw>Sol"o*mon's seal</hw>. <def>A mystic symbol consisting of two
interlaced triangles forming a star with six points, often with one
triangle dark and one light, symbolic of the union of soul and body. It
is shaped identically to the <er>hexagram</er> and <er>Star of
David</er>, distinguished only in its usage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Solon</ent>⟦br⟧
